headline: Citi (C) Profit Margin Rises to 17.8%, Challenging Bearish Sentiment on Turnaround
summary: Citigroup (C) posted a net profit margin of 17.8%, up from last year’s 9.7%, while earnings growth surged 100.6% over the past year, in stark contrast to a five-year average decline of 10.4% per year. Investors are eyeing this turnaround in profitability, especially as upcoming earnings are forecast to grow at 16.04% per year, outpacing the broader US market, despite more modest revenue growth projections.
